<h1>Create a New Artist</h1>

<%= form_for(@artist) do |f| %>
  <%= f.label :name, "Artist Name" %><br>
  <%= f.text_field :name %><br>
  <%= f.label :bio, "Artist Bio" %><br>
  <%= f.text_area :bio %><br>
  <%= f.submit %>
<% end %>

<!-- The form_for Rails form helper method above generates the following HTML <form> element:

<form class="new_artist" id="new_artist" accept-charset="UTF-8" action="/artists" method="POST">
  ...etc
  <input type="hidden" name="authenticity_token" value="token goes here">
  <label for="artist_name">Artist Name</label><br>
  <input type="text" name="artist[name]" id="artist_name"><br>
  <label for="artist_bio">Artist Bio</label><br>
  <textarea name="artist[bio]" id="artist_bio"></textarea><br>
  <input type="submit" name="commit" value="Create Artist">
</form>

Note: the second argument passed to f.label will change the text of the label from Name to Artist Name
